class Solution {
    public boolean canSortArray(int[] nums) {
        int lastCnt = 0;
        int lastGroupMax = 0;
        int curGroupMax = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            int curCnt = Integer.bitCount(num);
            if (curCnt == lastCnt) {
                curGroupMax = Math.max(curGroupMax, num);
            } else {
                lastCnt = curCnt;
                lastGroupMax = curGroupMax;
                curGroupMax = num;
            }
            if (num < lastGroupMax) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```
In this solution, we keep track of the last group maximum and the current group maximum, as well as the bit count of the last group. When we encounter a number with the same bit count as the last group, we update the current group maximum. Otherwise, we update the last group maximum to be the current group maximum and the current group maximum to be the current number. If at any point a number is less than the last group maximum, we return false, because this means that the current group maximum could be swapped with a number from the previous group, which would break the sortedness of the array. If we finish iterating through the array without finding such a number, we return true.

